	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65140943">"Given enough time" is doing a lot of work here. You can write a very simple program to play a 100% perfect game of chess, "given enough time" to roll out every potential move to the end of the game.
<p>
Especially when working with physical experimentation (which would include physics, or drug discovery) it's more like this: you have enough resources to do 100 trials (or 10, or 1000, whatever).  That's it.  So the better your heuristics to identify which things to try in the lab, the more scientific progress<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_65140943">

